# Copy to .env and fill in.
#   cp .env.example .env && $EDITOR .env
# Load it before a run:  set -a && . ./.env && set +a
#
# AUTH — pick ONE of three. takoqa runs unattended for a long time, so an
# API key is the most robust (it never expires); OAuth is fine for short,
# interactive runs.
#   1. API key (recommended for long --loop/--explore runs):
#        set ANTHROPIC_API_KEY below.
#   2. OAuth profile (auto-refreshed, like Claude Code — survives long runs):
#        run `ant auth login` once, then leave ANTHROPIC_API_KEY UNSET; the SDK
#        reads the on-disk profile and refreshes the token itself.
#   3. OAuth bearer token (short-lived, NOT auto-refreshed — expires mid-run):
#        set ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN instead (e.g. `eval "$(ant auth print-credentials --env)"`).
# Note: if ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is set (even to ""), it overrides the other two.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN=          # option 3 only; leave the key unset if you use this

# Optional — override the model (default: a current Claude model; see src/run.ts).
# QA_AGENT_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6

# Optional — defaults for CLI flags, so you don't repeat them every run.
# QA_AGENT_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3000
# QA_AGENT_BASELINE_DIR=./baseline
# QA_AGENT_LEARNED_DIR=./learned
# QA_AGENT_RECIPES_DIR=./recipes
